Reproductive system diorchic with two outstretched testes; anterior testis to the left and posterior testis to the right of intestine. Mature sperm cells nucleated, spherical to globular, 9 × 9–13 μm. Spicules 1.3 abd long, slightly arcuate, with swollen proximal ends and pointed distal ends. Gubernaculum and pre-cloacal supplements absent. Tail conico-cylindrical with conspicuous thickening of inner cuticle (maximum thickness ~7 μm) immediately anterior to cylindrical portion (
Fig. 5D
); cylindrical portion shorter than conical portion. A few short, sparse caudal setae present sub-ventrally and sub-dorsally; three short terminal setae, 2 μm long. Caudal glands not observed.
